    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1870-06-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1870-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="510"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoar</persName>, Attorney-General,
                        to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>, Secretary of State.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Attorney-General’s Office</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1870-06-11">
                        <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 11, 1870</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose a copy of the
                    instructions which have to-day been sent to the district attorney of North
                    Carolina, in relation to the settlement of the case of the Hornet, or Cuba, and
                    which are, I believe, in conformity with the wishes of the President, as
                    communicated by you to me. I inclose with them the bond which has been given by
                    the claimant of the vessel as a condition of the settlement, and a check for
                    twenty-five hundred dollars paid by the claimant in settlement of such of the
                    expenses incurred by the United States in relation to the witnesses, &amp;c., as
                    it has been agreed he should pay.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. R. HOAR,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Attorney-General.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton Fish</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
